comments.body:
In other cases we've used a single template method, instead of each type or case having its own explicit implementation - would it make sense to unify this as well?
```suggestion
template<typename T, SettingOptions options>
struct SettingTraits
{
    static bool Get(const SettingsValue& setting, T&)
    {
        if constexpr (std::is_same_v<T, Unset>) return setting.isNull();
        if constexpr (std::is_same_v<T, Enabled>) return setting.isTrue();
        if constexpr (std::is_same_v<T, Disabled>) return setting.isFalse();
        // ... other specializations (using options param as well)
        return false;
    }
};
```

